<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><!DOCTYPE paragraph PUBLIC "-//IFRS//DTD DITA Paragraph//EN" "../../../DocTypes/com.ifrs.doctype/dtd/paragraph.dtd"><paragraph id="IAS16_17" base="SL30298" principles="no"><paranum class="- topic/title paragraph/paranum "/><titlealts><navtitle>17</navtitle></titlealts><prolog><data name="standard_number" value="IAS 16"/><data name="paranum" value="17"/></prolog><body><bodydiv base="IAS2020-2">     <p id="IAS16_P0101" outputclass="keep_with_next">Examples of directly attributable costs are:</p>     <ol outputclass="static" id="IAS16_L0010" base="SL144248" type="lower-alpha"><li><li_value>(a)</li_value>         <p id="IAS16_P0102" base="SL144250">costs of employee benefits (as defined in <xref id="IAS16_X0133" base="F77792866" href="../ias19/IAS19_TOC0001.dita#IAS19_TOC0001">IAS 19 <ph outputclass="standard_ref"><ph outputclass="standard_title">Employee Benefits</ph></ph></xref>) arising directly from the construction or acquisition of the item of property, plant and equipment;</p>       </li><li><li_value>(b)</li_value>         <p id="IAS16_P0103" base="SL144252">costs of site preparation;</p>       </li><li><li_value>(c)</li_value>         <p id="IAS16_P0104" base="SL144254">initial delivery and handling costs;</p>       </li><li><li_value>(d)</li_value>         <p id="IAS16_P0105" base="SL144256">installation and assembly costs;</p>       </li><li><li_value>(e)</li_value>         <p id="IAS16_P0106" base="SL144258">costs of testing whether the asset is functioning properly (ie assessing whether the technical and physical performance of the asset is such that it is capable of being used in the production or supply of goods or services, for rental to others, or for administrative purposes); and</p>       </li><li><li_value>(f)</li_value>         <p id="IAS16_P0107" base="SL144260">professional fees.</p>       </li></ol></bodydiv></body></paragraph>